Responsibilities
Gather non functional requirements to define performance test strategies and design load test scenarios to mimic production workload;
Work in performance and load testing domain;
Design and conduct load tests using HP Performance center, Load Runner, Neoload and JMeter;
Create VUGEN scripts using protocols including web http/html, web services, Ajax, Mobile and Citrix;
Analyze test results to analyze and correlate with monitoring and diagnosis tools such as SiteScope, and Wily IntraScope;
Analyze architecture, relationship between systems, and systems flow of end-to-end designs in order to define the performance test strategy to uncover potential performance bottlenecks;
Create, develop and program the scripts to simulate user behavior and peak load conditions and projected volumes;
Collaborate and coordinate with the application teams, infrastructure teams, middleware, backend and network teams to conduct production level load tests;
Analyze the performance test results to assist application teams in root cause analysis by providing and correlating performance test results with monitoring and diagnostics data;
Use HP Performance center, Neoload, JMeter, Wily and SiteScope tools to exercise the tests and baseline software and hardware performance stats;
Document tests and test results to generate performance trend reports;
Plan, track and report enterprise performance testing projects to ensure timely completion.
Qualifications
Masterâ€™s or foreign equivalent degree in Computer Science or Computer Engineering and 2 years of experience in the job offered or 2 years of experience in performance and load testing domain; 2 years of experience designing and conducting load tests using HP Performance center, Load Runner, Neoload and JMeter; 2 years of experience creating VUGEN scripts using protocols including web http/html, web services, Ajax, Mobile and Citrix; 2 years of experience analyzing test results to analyze and correlate with monitoring and diagnosis tools such as SiteScope, and Wily IntraScope.
