Responsibilities
Key Areas of Responsibility:
Responsible for coordinating internal and external audits and compliance activities, preparing materials, and coordinating work;
Develop a compliance / controls tracking dashboard consolidating multiple compliance efforts;
Perform ongoing security audits to ensure that the security posture is not compromised;
Participate in security projects and program development;
Participate in application and network security assessments;
Perform global security assessments to ensure compliance with contractual and regulatory requirements;
Working with IT leadership and business groups in facilitating compliance requirements;
Development of sound security policies and procedures; and
Responsible for educating, monitoring, auditing, advising, and reporting of compliance efforts.
Qualifications
Basic Qualifications:
The position requires that the individual have a sense of urgency to address existing and new requirements for technologies being deployed;
The individual must hold themselves to the highest levels of personal and professional integrity;
Demonstrated ability to work effectively in an ambiguous environment;
Demonstrated ability to work across geographical locations;
Strong oral and written communications skills;
Strong analytical and problem solving skills and proactive thinking skills;
Proactive thinking, analytical thinking and problem solving skills;
5+ years of IT Security & Compliance experience;
4+ years of Project Management experience;
4+ years of IT Audit / Risk Management experience; and
Strong understanding of ISO27001, PCI, and SSAE 16 SOC requirements.
Preferred/Optional Skills:
Ability to participate in key proactive security programs and projects;
CISA, CISM, CISSP certifications preferred;
Incident Response Management; and/or
Experience working within a global security and/or compliance role.
Education:
Bachelors in management information systems, computer science, engineering or related technical field
Physical Requirements:
While performing the essential functions of this job, the employee is frequently required to sit; hear or talk: use close vision; use hands to grasp, handle or feel objects; and type and manipulate controls. Employee is occasionally required to use distance vision, stand, kneel or crouch and lift up to 10 lbs.
